==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aftermost
<hw>Aft"er*most</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a. superl.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>eftemest</ets>, AS. <ets>⟦ae⟧ftemest</ets>, akin to Gothic
<ets>aftumist</ets> and <ets>aftuma</ets>, the last, orig. a superlative
of <ets>of</ets>, with the superlative endings <ets>-te</ets>,
<ets>-me</ets>, <ets>-st</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Hindmost; --
opposed to <ant>foremost</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>Nearest the stern; most
aft.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Afternoon</ent>⟦br⟧
